---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-location.njk",
  "permalink": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/industries/restaurant/",
  "slug": "ny-ind-restaurant",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-hub",
  "bodyClass": "page--location page--industry",
  "callBar": true,
  "title": "New York Restaurant Accounting · TechBrot",
  "description": "Restaurant accounting for New York operators — POS reconciliation, NY tip-credit payroll, prepared-food sales tax, food & prime cost tracking. From $400/mo. Call (877) 751-5575.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Find an Accountant", "href": "/find-an-accountant/" },
    { "name": "New York", "href": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/" },
    { "name": "Industries", "href": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/industries/" },
    { "name": "Restaurant" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "New York &middot; Restaurants &amp; Hospitality",
    "heading": "New York restaurant accounting that gets tip wages and sales tax right.",
    "subheading": "In a thin-margin business, two New York rules can sink you &mdash; the tip-credit math on every paycheck and sales tax on prepared food. A named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor reconciles your POS to the bank, tracks food cost and prime cost, and keeps payroll and sales tax structured to New York&rsquo;s hospitality rules &mdash; all in your own QuickBooks file. We deliver the books; your CPA files.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=new-york&state=new-york&source_type=industry&funnel_stage=MOFU", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "New York operators start here",
    "heading": "Get tip wages, sales tax, and prime cost right — every month.",
    "lede": "Book a free discovery call. We&rsquo;ll look at your QuickBooks file and POS, show you where margin and compliance gaps are hiding, flag any tip-credit or prepared-food sales-tax exposure, and send a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days. No pitch. Independent firm &mdash; does not file NY taxes; coordinates with your CPA.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=new-york&state=new-york&source_type=industry&funnel_stage=BOFU", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the TL;DR prose. (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-ind-restaurant-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The short version.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: New York restaurant accounting, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-restaurant-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York restaurant accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-ind-restaurant-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CHALLENGES · three places NY restaurants lose money (grid-3 buyer-cards). (H2 + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-restaurant-challenges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why NY restaurant books leak margin</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three places New York restaurants lose money and risk penalties.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">In a business that lives on single-digit margins, each of these can be the difference between a profitable month and a loss. Knowing which one you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE HANDLE · the six services (grid-3 buyer-cards). (H2 + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-restaurant-handle">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What TechBrot handles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York restaurant accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to your concept and locations, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; coordinating with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTEGRATIONS · tools reconciled with QuickBooks (checks-list). (H2: Connected to how you run service.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-restaurant-integrations">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Tools we work alongside</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Connected to how you run service.</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for t in integrations %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose">{{ integrationsNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROCESS · four-phase engagement rhythm (grid-2 buyer-cards). (H2 + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-restaurant-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How engagements work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From bank-balance guessing to prime-cost control.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every New York restaurant engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; books accurate first, margin visibility second, advisory third.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ p.phase }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ p.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line carried as section prose. (H2: Controlling prime cost is the start. Building a profitable concept is the point.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-restaurant-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Controlling prime cost is the start. Building a profitable concept is the point.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=new-york&amp;state=new-york&amp;source_type=industry&amp;funnel_stage=BOFU">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 verbatim contract Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: New York restaurant accounting questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-restaurant-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York restaurant accounting questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-ind-restaurant-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-ind-restaurant-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name (byline-block + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-restaurant-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot handles New York restaurant and hospitality engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for technical accuracy on POS-to-bank reconciliation, food and prime cost, tip-credit payroll under the <a href="https://dol.ny.gov/minimum-wage-0" rel="noopener nofollow">NY Hospitality Wage Order</a>, and prepared-food sales tax (<a href="https://www.tax.ny.gov/" rel="noopener nofollow">NY DTF</a>). The 2026 tipped-wage rates, the 80/20 rule, and prepared-food taxability reflect NY Department of Labor and Tax Department guidance current as of the date below &mdash; confirm current rates before each payroll year. TechBrot delivers the books and coordinates with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-07</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-07</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-07 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · NY services & industries (grid-2 buyer-cards). (H2 + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-restaurant-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related New York services &amp; industries.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ r.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
